snVLanCARTable.name: snVLanCARTable
snVLanCARTable.description: A table of rate limit configuration entries for a vlan. Rate Limit is a method of traffic control. It allows a set of rate limits to be configured and applied to packets flowing into/out of an interface to regulate network traffic.

snVLanCAREntry.name: snVLanCAREntry
snVLanCAREntry.description: A collection of rate-limit configuration objects on this vlan.

snVLanCARVLanId.name: snVLanCARVLanId
snVLanCARVLanId.description: The VLAN ID as one of the indices of this table . Each VLAN ID can have a membership of multiple ports.

snVLanCARDirection.name: snVLanCARDirection
snVLanCARDirection.description: The input or output transmission direction for the Rate Limit object.

snVLanCARRowIndex.name: snVLanCARRowIndex
snVLanCARRowIndex.description: The table index for rate limit objects. It increases as the rate limit entries are added. Skips the number when a row is deleted.

snVLanCARType.name: snVLanCARType
snVLanCARType.description: The type of traffic rate-limited against.

snVLanCARAccIdx.name: snVLanCARAccIdx
snVLanCARAccIdx.description: The index to the access list if RateLimitType is either quickAcc or standardAcc.

snVLanCARRate.name: snVLanCARRate
snVLanCARRate.description: The comitted access rate. This determines the long term average transmission rate. Traffic that falls under this rate always conforms. This is average rate in bits per second.

snVLanCARLimit.name: snVLanCARLimit
snVLanCARLimit.description: This is the normal burst size that determines how large traffic bursts can be before some traffic exceeds the rate limit. This specifies the number of bytes that are guaranteed to be transported by the network at the average rate under normal conditions during committed time interval. This normal burst size is in bytes.

snVLanCARExtLimit.name: snVLanCARExtLimit
snVLanCARExtLimit.description: This is the extended burst limit that determines how large traffic bursts can be before all the traffic exceeds the rate limit. This burst size is in bytes.

snVLanCARConformAction.name: snVLanCARConformAction
snVLanCARConformAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic is within the Rate Limit. drop drop the packet. xmit transmit the packet. continue continue to evaluate to the subsequent rate limits. precedXmit rewrite the IP precedence and transmit the packet. precedCont rewrite the IP precedence and allow it evaluated by subsequent rate limits.

snVLanCARExceedAction.name: snVLanCARExceedAction
snVLanCARExceedAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the Rate Limit. drop drop the packet. xmit transmit the packet. continue continue to evaluate to the subsequent rate limits. precedXmit rewrite the IP precedence and transmit the packet. precedCont rewrite the IP precedence and allow it evaluated by subsequent rate limits.

snVLanCARStatSwitchedPkts.name: snVLanCARStatSwitchedPkts
snVLanCARStatSwitchedPkts.description: The counter of packets permitted by this rate limit.

snVLanCARStatSwitchedBytes.name: snVLanCARStatSwitchedBytes
snVLanCARStatSwitchedBytes.description: The counter of bytes permitted by this interface.

snVLanCARStatFilteredPkts.name: snVLanCARStatFilteredPkts
snVLanCARStatFilteredPkts.description: The counter of packets which exceeded this rate limit.

snVLanCARStatFilteredBytes.name: snVLanCARStatFilteredBytes
snVLanCARStatFilteredBytes.description: The counter of bytes which exceeded this rate limit.
